\chapter{The resident engine: MI.U1}

\texttt{MI.U1} (``machine interface'') is the game's memory-resident
core, occupying [[$7000]]--[[$89BC]] --- everything below the overlay
region at [[OVERLAY_ENTRY]]. It supplies the services every mode
overlay shares: the status panel, text output, the player-disk save
files (\texttt{/U1.PLAYER}, \texttt{/U1.VARS} --- their pathnames are
in the string region), name tables for items, monsters, and places,
and assorted drawing helpers. Its first instruction simply jumps to
the overlay entry point: running \texttt{MI.U1} \emph{is} running
whichever overlay is currently loaded at [[OVERLAY_ENTRY]].

The engine code ([[$8037]]--[[$89BC]]) is now fully decomposed; two
data regions remain as classified stubs:

\begin{itemize}
\item [[MIU1_TABLES]] --- graphics data, including the 10-byte-wide
  death image that [[DEATH]] blits (runs of [[$FF]], [[$E0]],
  [[$83]] pixel patterns).
\item [[MIU1_STRINGS]] --- roughly 2.6K of packed text: the race,
  class, item, weapon, spell, and command name tables (their entry
  points are EQU'd below, [[STR_RACES]] through [[STR_COMMANDS]]),
  prompts, and the save-file
  pathnames. The engine's player state block ([[$7E05]]--[[$8036]],
  inside [[MIU1_CODE_A]]) holds the live character data; both are
  carved in the next rounds.
\end{itemize}

<<miu1 defines>>=
RESET_VEC       EQU $03F2       ; ProDOS soft-reset vector (+2: check)
MON_HOME        EQU $FC58       ; monitor: clear the text screen
MON_RESET       EQU $FF59       ; monitor cold entry (placeholder)
@

<<miu1 entry>>=
        ORG $7000
MIU1_ENTRY
        ; the resident engine starts whatever overlay is loaded
        JMP OVERLAY_ENTRY
@ %def MIU1_ENTRY

<<miu1 mask tables>>=
        ORG $7003
MIU1_TABLES
        ; STUB — not yet disassembled (bitmask/graphics tables)
        HEX 00 00 00 00 fe bf 00 00
        HEX 00 00 00 00 00 e0 ff ff
        HEX 83 00 00 00 00 00 00 f8
        HEX ff ff 8f 00 00 00 00 00
        HEX 00 ff ff ff ff 00 00 00
        HEX 00 00 e0 ff ff ff ff 81
        HEX 00 00 00 00 f8 ff ff ff
        HEX ff 87 00 00 00 00 fc ff
        HEX ff ff ff 9f 00 00 00 00
        HEX ff ff ff ff ff ff 00 00
        HEX 00 00 ff ff ff ff ff ff
        HEX 81 00 00 e0 ff ff ff ff
        HEX ff ff 83 00 00 e0 ff ff
        HEX ff ff ff ff 87 00 00 f0
        HEX ff ff ff ff ff ff 8f 00
